    "# 02 — Embedding Comparison: Small-Dataset Fraud Detection Strategy\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goal:** Compare text representations suited for ~170 samples, keeping evaluation consistent.  \n",
    "**Dataset path:** `C:/Users/user/Documents/data_science_bootcamp_challenges_project/capstone_project/amit_kedia_dataset.csv`\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why This Notebook Was Redesigned\n",
    "\n",
    "The original notebook used FinBERT fine-tuning and general BERT — both require thousands of samples to generalize.  \n",
    "At **170 samples**, the right strategy is:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Principle | Reasoning |\n",
    "|-----------|----------|\n",
    "| **Freeze all transformer weights** | Fine-tuning = overfitting at this scale |\n",
    "| **Use domain-specific frozen encoders** | SEC-BERT > FinBERT for SEC filings |\n",
    "| **Prefer SVM over Logistic Regression** | SVM handles small, imbalanced data better |\n",
    "| **Ensemble multiple signals** | Combines lexical + semantic strengths |\n",
    "| **Cross-validation over train/test split** | With 170 samples, any single split is noisy |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Techniques Compared\n",
    "\n",
    "| # | Embedding | Classifier | Rationale |\n",
    "|---|-----------|------------|-----------|\n",
    "| 1 | TF-IDF (baseline) | SVM | Lexical fraud signals; interpretable |\n",
    "| 2 | TF-IDF | Logistic Regression | Same as original for direct comparison |\n",
    "| 3 | Frozen SEC-BERT | SVM | Domain-matched encoder for SEC filings |\n",
    "| 4 | Frozen FinBERT | SVM | Previous approach, now frozen (no fine-tuning) |\n",
    "| 5 | Hybrid TF-IDF + SEC-BERT | SVM | Combines lexical + semantic features |\n",
    "| 6 | Isolation Forest on SEC-BERT | Unsupervised | Anomaly detection — no labels needed |"
